Accessibility Namespace

Definition

The Accessibility and all of its exposed members are part of a managed wrapper for the Component Object Model (COM) accessibility interface.

In this Article

Classes

CAccPropServicesClass

The CAccPropServicesClass and all of its exposed members are part of a managed wrapper for the Component Object Model (COM) IAccPropServices interface.

The __MIDL_IWinTypes_0009 and all of its exposed members are part of a managed wrapper for the Component Object Model (COM) accessibility interface.
_RemotableHandle

The IAccessibleHandler and all of its exposed members are part of a managed wrapper for the Component Object Model (COM) accessibility interface.

The IAccessible interface and all of its exposed members are part of a managed wrapper for the Component Object Model (COM) IAccessible interface.
IAccessibleHandler

The IAccessibleHandler and all of its exposed members are part of a managed wrapper for the Component Object Model (COM) IAccessibleHandler interface.

The IAccIdentity and all of its exposed members are part of a managed wrapper for the Component Object Model (COM) IAccIdentity interface.

The IAccPropServer and all of its exposed members are part of a managed wrapper for the Component Object Model (COM) IAccPropServer interface.

Remarks

For more information about Accessibility, see the Microsoft Active Accessibility documentation in the MSDN library at http://msdn.microsoft.com/library.
